SLA = {'pine': 6.8, 'spruce': 4.7, 'birch': 14.0}  # Hrknen et al. 2015 BER 20, 181-195

Loop through spcies, load subset of mNFI data¶

  1. Select stands (species volume / total volume >0.9), mineral soil (maintype=1), all sitetypes
  2. Fit non-linear model BMf = a + b[1 -exp(cVol)] to predict foliage biomass [kg ha-1] from stem volume [m3 ha-1]

See mNFI description in Readme-2019.txt

def density_scatter(x , y, ax=None, sort=True, bins=20, axis_labels=['x','y'], **kwargs )   :
    """
    Scatter plot colored by point density from 2d histogram
    from: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/20105364/how-can-i-make-a-scatter-plot-colored-by-density-in-matplotlib
    """
    if ax is None :
        fig , ax = plt.subplots()
    data , x_e, y_e = np.histogram2d( x, y, bins=bins, density=True )
    z = interpn( ( 0.5*(x_e[1:] + x_e[:-1]) , 0.5*(y_e[1:]+y_e[:-1]) ) , data , np.vstack([x,y]).T , method = "splinef2d", bounds_error = False)

    #To be sure to plot all data
    z[np.where(np.isnan(z))] = 0.0

    # Sort the points by density, so that the densest points are plotted last
    if sort :
        idx = z.argsort()
        x, y, z = x[idx], y[idx], z[idx]

    ax.scatter( x, y, c=z, **kwargs )
    ax.set_xlabel(axis_labels[0])
    ax.set_ylabel(axis_labels[1])
    
    norm = Normalize(vmin = np.min(z), vmax = np.max(z))
    cbar = plt.colorbar(cm.ScalarMappable(norm = norm), ax=ax)
    cbar.ax.set_ylabel('point density')

    return ax

#--- ba - foliage mass

def bef_lehtonen(x, a, b):
    # y = a*x**b # Lehtonen et al. 2004 eq.3: Biomass = a * Vol**b
    # using ln: log(a*x**b) = log(a) + b*log(x)
    #a = log(a), b = b x = log(x)
    #returns log(y)
    y = a + b*x
    return y

def bef_nonlinear(x, a, b):
    #non-linear, fits well to binned mVMI data
    y =  a * (1 - np.exp(-b*x))
    return y
